frameDefinitions: A Person is in a state of prosperity and/or renown after some period of development or hardship in an Endeavor.
This frame contains verbs that describe emotional experiences and participate in the locative alternation, as in the following examples: '' ' I was boiling with anger.'
An Astronomical_entity comes into view above the horizon as part of a regular, periodic process of (apparent) motion of the Astronomical_entity across the sky.
An Item is in a state of wetness with the possibility of the wetting Liquid being mentioned, along with the Degree of wetness. '
An Agent or a Cause causes a Fluid to move from a Source to a Goal along a Path or within an Area.
An Excreter excretes Excreta. 'Principal Skinner burped on me.'
frameExamples: Venus <t>rose</t> at 5:23 AM, twenty minutes before the sun which reached the horizon at 5:43 AM.
The mop is <t>drenched</t> with water from last night's rain.
listRoleDefinitions: A sentient being or group of beings that is prosperous or well known after being involved in some <fen>Endeavor</fen>.
An event that the <fen>Person</fen> is involved in which leads to their state of prosperity or renown.
The time when the <fen>Entity</fen> is determined to be successful.
The Experiencer is the individual that experiences the <fen>Emotion</fen>.

The Emotion experienced (usually restricted to words such as <ment>anger, fury, rage, passion</ment>) can occur as the External Argument or in a PP Complement. Alternatively, there may be no expression of Emotion separate from the target verb:
The words in this frame can occur with an overtly expressed Seat of the Emotion. This frame element occurs as a PP Complement:
An entity which is periodically visible from the earth's surface.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Astronomical_entity</fen> appears.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> from which the motion of the <fen>Astronomical_entity</fen> is viewed.
The <fen>Item</fen> takes up the <fen>Liquid</fen> through its pores.
The <fen>Liquid</fen> is a fluid or gas that permeates the <fen>Item</fen>.  It most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with.
The animate protagonist who causes the <fen>Fluid</fen> to move.
An event or force that causes the <fen>Fluid</fen> to move.
The entity that changes location and moves in a fluidic way. It is not necessarily in a liquid state but is construed that way.
The location that the <fen>Fluid</fen> occupies initially.
<fen>Goal</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> ends up in as a result  of the motion
The trajectory along which the Fluid moves, exclusive of the <fen>Source</fen> and <fen>Goal</fen>.
The setting in which the <fen>Fluid</fen>'s movement takes place along an unspecified <fen>Path</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the fluidic motion event is caused.
The location where the motion takes place.
The <fen>Excreta</fen> is the waste expelled by the body.
The <fen>Excreter</fen> is the agent who excretes the <fen>Excreta</fen>.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the starting point of the <fen>Excreta</fen>'s motion.
When the <fen>Excreter</fen> engages in excretion.
This role identifieis the <fen>Place</fen> where the excretion occurs.
listRoleExamples: <fex>He</fex> became a success at the age of 25.
Looking back, I had a very successful <fex>career</fex>.
After 20 years of hard work, he finally made it as an artist <fex>in '84</fex>.
Heku left one morning as <fex>the sun</fex> rose along the plain.
As the sun came up <fex>at 5:15 am</fex>, it made the red rocks almost glow.
The very end of the eclipse will be visible as the sun rises <fex>in some locations in Africa and northeastern North America</fex>.
The mop was drenched <fex> with water</fex>.
What happens if <fex>we</fex> drip acid on this compound?
Why did  you squirt juice <fex>onto my chair</fex>?
I spattered the egg all over the floor <fex>in the kitchen</fex>.
Dr. Nick vomited <fex>puke</fex> across the table.
